{"TopicId":149758,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"[Request] 1.2 Improve map-view signal lines by removing opacity","CreatedByName":"Bayesian","CreatedById":170108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-12T07:26:28Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Bayesian","CreatedById":170108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-12T07:26:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProblem\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E: In map-view lines are shown between all your\u00A0Communications Network connections. These lines\u00A0become more opaque(see through) as the signal strength decreases. Even though there is a sufficient connect\u00A0\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Ethe lines become invisible when over the dark starry background.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00229dXEchS.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/9dXEchS.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#008000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESolution\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E: Either completely remove opacity, keeping only the green to red scale for signal strength \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eor\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u00A0significantly increase its minimal\u00A0opacity. \u003Cem\u003EMaybe\u003C/em\u003E also adjust colors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022cfi45gF.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/cfi45gF.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI would really like to see this small UI improvement made to the\u00A0Communications Network\u00A0signal strength lines\u00A0in map-view. I\u0027m looking for someone to either just take my idea and make it or help me in making it myself. My programming skills are pretty vague,\u00A0Visual Studio 2015\u00A0is all set up \u00A0and the .dlls are imported and I\u0027m aware of\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalspaceprogram.com/api/annotated.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalspaceprogram.com/api/annotated.html\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0but I have no idea what classes to use or\u00A0where the opacity variables\u00A0are. I\u0027ll continue to try; any help or suggestions are appreciated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-12T07:38:05Z\u0022 title=\u002210/12/2016 07:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 12, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bayesian\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-12T09:23:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhum, there is a slider in the settings...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bayesian","CreatedById":170108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-12T09:29:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the reply.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222799223\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149758\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476264233\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257146\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sarbian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, sarbian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhum, there is a slider in the settings...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat changes the antenna\u0027s \u003Cu\u003Eactual\u003C/u\u003E range. I want the difficulty unchanged but would like to actually be able\u00A0see the lines..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-12T11:50:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... No there are options to change the opacity. At minimum it is in the cfg\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bayesian","CreatedById":170108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-12T12:37:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222799408\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149758\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476273028\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257146\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sarbian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, sarbian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... No there are options to change the opacity. At minimum it is in the cfg\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m a bit confused, I\u0027ve looked everywhere 3 times and I can\u0027t find what you\u0027re talking about, I don\u0027t think its there because:\u003Cbr\u003E\n1. There is no\u00A0 \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003Eopacity/alpha sliders anywhere in the in-game settings.\u003Cbr\u003E\n2. in the .cfg @\u00A0line 69:\u00A0UI_OPACITY = 0.5 which gets rest after closing the game but even with the file set to read only setting it to 1.0 or 0.1 does nothing at all anywhere as far as I can tell.\u003Cbr\u003E\n3. I don\u0027t see why this \u003Cu\u003Ewould be\u003C/u\u003E a user changeable setting at all, its a\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Efeature \u003C/em\u003Eworking as intended\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003E\u003Ci\u003E;\u00A0\u003C/i\u003Ethe lines get more faint as the signal gets more faint, it just does so way too much.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSorry if I\u0027m still not getting something.Thanks for trying help! \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HvP","CreatedById":146104,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-13T19:15:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/170108-bayesian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022170108\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/170108-bayesian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Bayesian\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, it\u0027s in the Main Menu / Settings / Graphics\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnder the Rendering column look for the slider labeled \u0022CommNet Line Brightness Factor.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis can also be changed from the in-game Escape menu settings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that\u0027s what you\u0027re looking for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-13T19:16:53Z\u0022 title=\u002210/13/2016 07:16  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by HvP\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bayesian","CreatedById":170108,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-14T09:55:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222802306\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149758\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476386115\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146104\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HvP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, HvP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/170108-bayesian/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022170108\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/170108-bayesian/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Bayesian\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, it\u0027s in the Main Menu / Settings / Graphics\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnder the Rendering column look for the slider labeled \u0022CommNet Line Brightness Factor.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis can also be changed from the in-game Escape menu settings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that\u0027s what you\u0027re looking for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerfect, thank you guys you\u0027re awesome.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nedit: Just to note, these settings are not in 1.2pre that\u0027s why I missed them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-14T09:56:12Z\u0022 title=\u002210/14/2016 09:56  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 14, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Bayesian\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}